theorem Topology.interiorClosure_iter8_idempotent
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior
      (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure A)))))))))))))) =
      interior (closure A) := by
  -- Start with the 7-fold idempotence lemma.
  have h :=
    Topology.interiorClosure_iter7_idempotent (A := A)
  -- Apply one more `interior ∘ closure` to both sides.
  have h' :
      interior (closure
        (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior
          (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure A)))))))))))) =
        interior (closure (interior (closure A))) := by
    simpa using congrArg (fun S : Set X => interior (closure S)) h
  -- Reduce the right-hand side via the basic idempotence lemma.
  have h'' :
      interior (closure (interior (closure A))) = interior (closure A) :=
    Topology.interiorClosure_idempotent (A := A)
  simpa [h''] using h'

theorem Topology.P3_mono {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hAB : A ⊆ B) (hP3B : Topology.P3 B) : Topology.P3 A := by
  dsimp [Topology.P3] at hP3B ⊢
  intro x hxA
  -- From `A ⊆ B` and `hP3B`, obtain membership in `interior (closure B)`.
  have hxIntB : x ∈ interior (closure B) := hP3B (hAB hxA)
  -- Monotonicity of `closure` and `interior` gives
  -- `interior (closure B) ⊆ interior (closure A)`.
  have hIncl : interior (closure B) ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
    interior_mono (closure_mono hAB)
  exact hIncl hxIntB

theorem Topology.interiorClosure_inter_interSubset
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (closure (A ∩ interior B)) ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
  -- We start with the basic inclusion `A ∩ interior B ⊆ A`.
  have h₀ : (A ∩ interior B : Set X) ⊆ A := by
    intro x hx
    exact hx.1
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions, giving
  -- `closure (A ∩ interior B) ⊆ closure A`.
  have h₁ : closure (A ∩ interior B) ⊆ closure A :=
    closure_mono h₀
  -- Finally, apply monotonicity of `interior`.
  exact interior_mono h₁
